    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>The new snow and wind slabs represent the main danger. Above approximately 1800 m the wind slabs are larger. Wind slabs are to be evaluated with care and prudence.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of new snow and a strong to storm force northeasterly wind, sometimes avalanche prone wind slabs will form in particular in places that are protected from the wind. In all aspects medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large slab avalanches are possible.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>A lot of snow will fall. In some places new snow and wind slabs are lying on a moist old snowpack.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
